5:
Good evening, beautiful. A night sky
like this is a fitting backdrop for your
majesty.
12:
Cut the flattery. What is it that you
really wish to speak about?
16:
I am Remnithâ€”guardian of dragons
and admirer of your beauty.
19:
I've got questions I want to ask...
about my sister who turned into a
dragon.
23:
...Would you fetch Stella and the
others? They'll likely want to hear
this too.
31:
Only once. We had a small chat
before she took off for
who-knows-where.
36:
If only you could have met your
sister as well, Remnith...
40:
That's all right. The important thing
is that I know she's safe...
45:
Ah, who am I kidding. I'm super
curious. What did you and Enith talk
about? Do you remember?
49:
Of course. How could I forget
anything that pure-hearted child
said?
52:
She claimed that she became a
dragon of her own volition.
55:
That girl was filled with so much
rage, it pained her.
58:
Raised as a guardian, only to have
to kill her charges when they posed
a threat to others...
61:
She couldn't stand that these
dragons were doomed to madness
and had to be put down.
64:
Her life now is spent searching for a
way to save the dragons from this
fate.
68:
...Just like I thought. If only I'd noticed
sooner, she wouldn't have had to go
at it alone...
73:
Is there... really no way to save the
dragons that have lost control?
77:
...She asked me the same thing, you
know.
80:
But my answer hasn't changed.
Those who become serpents lose
their sense of self immediately upon
transforming.
83:
At that point, they themselves are
incapable of wishing for salvation.
86:
And yet... despite learning this, your
sister's fury held strong.
89:
Freed from her duties as guardian,
she could've chosen to live a quiet
life with you instead.
92:
But she did not. Like sister, like
brother, I suppose.
96: ...I'll bet that's not all she said to you.
99:
Knowing her, she definitely would've
pointed out that you're just as angry
as she is about the cruelty of it all.
106:
A-Anbach! We've got an emergency
on our hands!
109:
E-everyone in the cave suddenly
froze up and collapsed in pain!
129:
If we let the transformation
complete, they'll only sufferâ€”
136: Get out of the way, Faf!
141: No! This isn't what they want!
144:
I can hear them! They're all saying
they want to play with you more,
Anbach!
152:
I'm not doing this because I wish for
it. If given the choice, I...
162: I also want to save them.
171:
Might as well give it a go. What've
we got to lose?
179: I refuse to be a slave to fate!
197:
I see. So there's no guarantee that
you can pull off that trick again.
201:
In case you didn't notice, my hands
were too full to be keeping notes of
the process.
204:
Besides, I'm fairly certain we only
succeeded because we got to them
before they were fully turned into
serpents...
214:
I don't know how it worked. I was
filled with the strong desire to save
them and felt myself move.
218:
Neither Rams nor Rustamov ever
told me about the goddess
resonating with dragons before...
221:
At any rate, we were lucky this time
around, but that won't always be the
case.
227:
But we pulled it off at least once.
That means we can do it again.
231:
I agree. As long as you two are here,
I feel like I can do anything.
235:
...If you all are going to do whatever
you like, then maybe I should as well.
238:
I'm tired of being pushed around by
you children anyway.
241:
It's about time I indulged my own
whims.
